--This is a small rust program in which we are tried to cover all scalar data types:--
1.int
2.float
3.string literals
4.boolean

--Also know we have covered about functions in rust:--
1.non argument + non return value(void)
2.non argument + return value
3.argument + no return value
4.argument + return value

syntax:  
        fn function_name()->(type of return value or can be void based on your program){
            
            //return statment;
            //writing return is optional we can directly type value without(;)
        }

Note: 
1.fn main() -> it is our entry point for the application.
2.In Rust the identfiers,members,function_name should be in snake_case.
2.We have seen some lifetime concepts(&'static str) which we will be seeing in future.
